{"key":"processedPost-15162256","value":{"id":15162256,"first":15146819,"last":16478879,"when":1317493639,"utime":"10/01/11 09:27 PM","content":"What I was saying is this: For a given amount of spawn,<br /><br />If you make one tub at a 1:1 ratio, or ten tubs at a 1:10 ratio, you will have used the same amount of spawn, but your results will give more total product on the latter.&nbsp; BE will be lower on the latter as well, but total harvest will be more.&nbsp; This is what is meant by a point of diminishing returns, not that using a lower spawn rate is inferior, provided one pasteurizes properly and gets the substrate colonized before contamination takes over.<br /><br />It makes no difference if one is growing commercially or not.&nbsp; Getting maximum product per pound of spawn is simply getting maximum product.&nbsp; Also remember, cubensis is a great training species for more advanced work later on, but don't think you're going to be keeping those training wheels bolted to your bike forever.&nbsp; I know of very few growers who only grew cubensis ten years ago who even care one whit about them today.&nbsp; If one is seriously into the psilocybes, there's far better species to grow than cubes. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\":wink:\"/><br />RR","title":"Re: whats your input to output ratio doing bulk grains?"}}